1. Transitioning to Technical Planning
Technical Requirements:
•	Frontend Requirements:
o	Responsive and intuitive UI using Next.js, Typescript and Tailwind CSS.
o	Dynamic product catalog with filtering and sorting options.
o	User account management (login, registration, profile update).
o	Order tracking and history.
•	Backend Requirements:
o	Sanity CMS for managing product and content data.
o	Integration with third-party APIs for payment processing and shipment tracking.
o	Secure authentication and authorization.
•	Third-Party APIs:
o	Payment gateway API (e.g., Stripe, PayPal).
o	Shipment tracking API (e.g., Shippo, EasyPost).
o	Geolocation API for delivery zone coverage.
2. Design System Architecture
System Components:
•	Frontend (Next.js, Typescript with Tailwind CSS).
•	Backend and Database ( integrated with Sanity CMS).
•	APIs (Third-party services for payment and shipment).
High-Level Diagram:
•	User interacts with the frontend.
•	Frontend communicates with the backend.
•	Backend interacts with:
o	Sanity CMS for product data.
o	Database for orders and customers.
o	Third-party APIs for payment and shipment.
Key Workflows:
•	User Registration:
1.	User submits registration form.
2.	Backend validates and stores data.
3.	Confirmation email sent to user.
•	Product Browsing:
1.	User selects category or applies filters.
2.	Backend fetches product data from Sanity CMS.
3.	Results displayed on the frontend.
•	Order Placement:
1.	User adds products to cart and proceeds to checkout.
2.	Backend calculates total price and creates an order.
3.	Payment processed via third-party API.
•	Shipment Tracking:
1.	User enters order ID to track shipment.
2.	Backend fetches tracking data from shipment API.
3.	Tracking status displayed to user.
3. Plan API Requirements
Frontend to Backend APIs:
•	User Registration:
o	Method: POST
o	Endpoint: /api/register
o	Body: {
 name, 
email, 
password, 
address, 
phone_number }
•	Product Browsing:
o	Method: GET
o	Endpoint: /api/products
o	Query Params: {
 category, 
price_range, 
sort }
•	Order Placement:
o	Method: POST
o	Endpoint: /api/orders
o	Body: { customer_id,
o	 product_ids, 
o	total_price, 
o	payment_method }
•	Shipment Tracking:
o	Method: GET
o	Endpoint: /API/track-shipment
o	Query Params: { order_id }
Backend to Third-Party APIs:
•	Payment processing API integration.
•	Shipment tracking API integration.
•	Geolocation API for delivery zones.





